- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper discusses using modulation with nonuniform probability distribution of symbols to improve energy efficiency of transmission. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper focuses on improving energy efficiency of remote sensors in wireless telecommunication technology. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper discusses models and methods for nonuniform probability modulations. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper mentions using OFDM subcarriers for modulation. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly discuss security or cryptography, but it may be relevant in the context of wireless communication.
